                            <comment id="16915504" author="jsyrjala" created="Mon, 26 Aug 2019 06:07:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Related discussion:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://ask.clojure.org/index.php/8450/strange-behavior-with-clojure-java-io-copy&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ask.clojure.org/index.php/8450/strange-behavior-with-clojure-java-io-copy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16917000" author="bodewig" created="Tue, 27 Aug 2019 18:54:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m afraid &lt;tt&gt;Deflate64CompressorInputStream&lt;/tt&gt; is far from being the only stream out there that may return 0 sometimes. I agree this is in violation of the &lt;tt&gt;InputStream&lt;/tt&gt; contract but you should better be prepared to find more implementations with similar bugs outside of Compress as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16920950" author="bodewig" created="Mon, 2 Sep 2019 16:04:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a quick update.&#160;&lt;tt&gt;Deflate64CompressorInputStream&lt;/tt&gt; has been fixed in &lt;tt&gt;master&lt;/tt&gt; and I believe there is no other stream in Compress that will behave the same unless the wrapped stream or channel does.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
